<br>
Why is this important?  Many of us are getting to raid/epic age; we are going to start wanting to do things that we as a guild do not have the resources to do alone.  In order for us to have support for our own raid/epic-level encounters, we need to support those organized by others.<br>
<br>
I think we're all behind this in principle.  What can we do to make it happen?<br>
<br>
1) Those of you already over the 45 hurdle... please represent us at TGA events.  The calendar is linked at the top of the hunting packs page.  There are upcoming Plane of Air and City of Mist raids that some of us can attend.  When I get to 45, I will be looking to represent us at these events, but one 'count me in' wolf alone is not going to get us into TGA.   I will also be entering the old-world-dragon raiding scene, and any of you who want to give it a try, nudge me and I'll fill you in on what I know.  I'm hoping that I'll be ready for dragons in a couple of weeks - if you wanna go with, talk to me about resist gear and other dragon-raid stuff I'm learning.<br>
<br>
2) We have repeatedly been invited to Stormraven raids.  We've repeatedly not gotten back to them.  I know we as a guild have a great opinion of them... so why are we so apathetic on making this alliance happen? They are raiding ToFS on Sunday of this week, and have invited us to contribute a small force.  Since Sable and Harm were invited directly, I'm going.  There is an open-ended 'and others' to this invitation, so... are there a few 'others' (high 30's + please) who will go with us?  How about an elder or two to shake hands and make this alliance get moving?<br>
<br>
I am aware that Forin is planning a AW raid in ToFS.  This is not a substitute to that raid, this is an additional bonus-raid.<br>
<br>
I'm determined that I'm going to be a raiding bard.  I think there is a great desire in our guild to get our paw in the door of the raiding community - let's make this happen.  <br>
<br>
Harmonae Brooksong<br>
Bardess of 42nd Ditty<br>
